1
00:00:00,770 --> 00:00:03,350
It would be wonderful
[Brief Wind, Light Clouds]

2
00:00:03,350 --> 00:00:06,020
if we could continue living at Four Seasons Mountain Villa forever, just like this.

3
00:00:08,900 --> 00:00:14,410
[Faraway Wanderers]

4
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:42,100
♫ The sky is gray as I cross the cold river,
my duties taken care of ♫

5
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:49,250
♫ Smiling at the absurdity of the moon's reflection in my cup ♫

6
00:00:49,250 --> 00:00:55,030
♫ Who allowed me to roam around the world on horseback? ♫

7
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:56,990
I want to bet

8
00:00:56,990 --> 00:00:58,520
that you

9
00:01:00,140 --> 00:01:02,630
are the one I know.

10
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:11,880
♫ The cold rain of autumn kisses my windows ♫

11
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:19,370
♫  I don't mind hate and slander, but my melancholy persists ♫

12
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:22,370
♫ The spring breeze brings greenery along the river  ♫

13
00:01:22,370 --> 00:01:26,850
Are we meeting again in the martial arts world?

14
00:01:26,850 --> 00:01:33,890
♫ Is that our light that appeared out of nowhere? ♫

15
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:38,320
♫ I resent being unable to meet you earlier, but it is not too late ♫

16
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:42,070
♫ Don't let the flowers of the seasons down ♫

17
00:01:42,070 --> 00:01:50,050
♫ Give up the adventures on horseback for a peaceful,
quiet life by the stream ♫

18
00:01:50,050 --> 00:01:53,520
♫ The lights of thousands of families light up thousands of hills ♫

19
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:57,320
♫ The past disappears like smoke waves in a sandstorm ♫

20
00:01:57,320 --> 00:02:04,380
♫ I will clear away my cold past and happily spend the rest
of my life making wine and tea with you ♫

21
00:02:09,110 --> 00:02:10,800
A'Xu!

22
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:14,510
I used to think you were faking madness and pretending to be dumb.

23
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:16,870
I never expected that you would actually be insane.

24
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:24,320
♫ The grass grows along the mist-covered river as the flowing clouds reflect the sunset ♫

25
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:31,620
♫ Where is my homeland of shoulder blades and jade? ♫

26
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:35,900
I bet that one day that you will show me your true self.

27
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:39,140
♫ Why not split some to me? ♫

28
00:02:39,140 --> 00:02:46,320
♫ Drink together for three nights and never
speak of sorrowful farewells ♫

29
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:54,530
♫ I resent being unable to meet you earlier, but it is not too late;
don't let the flowers of the seasons down ♫

30
00:02:55,350 --> 00:02:58,390
I can't afford the things I want,

31
00:02:58,390 --> 00:03:02,530
and it is too late to hold on to the people I want.

32
00:03:02,530 --> 00:03:05,910
♫ The lights of thousands of families light up thousands of hills ♫

33
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:09,710
♫ The past disappears like smoke waves in a sandstorm ♫

34
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:17,200
♫ I will clear away my cold past and happily spend the rest
of my life making wine and tea with you ♫

35
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,080
Old Wen...

36
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,640
I thought I could change you slowly.

37
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:27,480
Who would've thought that I would be the one who ended up changing.

38
00:03:34,530 --> 00:03:36,800
I didn't know when you would come or how you would come,

39
00:03:39,070 --> 00:03:43,110
but I knew you would definitely come.

40
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:47,930
♫ The trees fall boundlessly ♫

41
00:03:49,070 --> 00:03:50,590
There is light

42
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:55,010
on your body. Let me catch it and see.

43
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:02,960
♫ Raise the voice to sing when victorious and rest when not ♫

44
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:06,810
♫ Unrestrained and unhindered ♫

45
00:04:06,810 --> 00:04:14,580
♫ Gaining a soulmate who can provide comfort
where the wind and dust is helpless ♫

46
00:04:14,580 --> 00:04:23,010
♫ No matter the height of the mountains or distance
of the sea, I will be with you ♫

47
00:05:00,650 --> 00:05:02,980
Please teach me, Elder!

48
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:08,060
Very good. Very good.

49
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:10,370
When my disciple was your age,

50
00:05:10,370 --> 00:05:13,420
he was far worse than you. The only skill that can be improved is that

51
00:05:13,420 --> 00:05:15,690
you are slightly hesitant in drawing your sword.

52
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:18,330
You are still inexperienced in battle.

53
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:20,970
The sword is the ruler of all weapons.

54
00:05:20,970 --> 00:05:22,650
It must uphold righteousness

55
00:05:22,650 --> 00:05:27,240
and must be unwavering in order to overrun all obstacles.

56
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:29,280
That won't work. Won't work.

57
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:35,860
One with a weapon must walk the ghostly path.

58
00:05:39,570 --> 00:05:42,950
Their movements must be unpredictable.

59
00:05:45,590 --> 00:05:49,250
A'Xu, you're teaching someone else's disciple again?

60
00:05:51,140 --> 00:05:57,570
♫ Every step is frightening and the moon has no light ♫

61
00:05:57,570 --> 00:06:04,640
♫ I pointed my sword into the dark night fearlessly ♫

62
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,520
That's you.

63
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:18,880
♫ Turns out that the world is vast and the earth's dust is insignificant, without you or me ♫

64
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:25,310
♫ Who freely comes and goes but implicates
fate for their hardships? ♫

65
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:32,490
♫ Our dreamscapes turned out to be so short,
the years pattering by, I lost myself ♫

66
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:39,910
♫ If an exhausted bird is unwilling, then best send it home ♫

67
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:45,150
All right. Let's go home and eat.

68
00:06:45,150 --> 00:06:47,170
Father, did I perform badly?

69
00:06:47,170 --> 00:06:49,280
Mother said I practiced very well.

70
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:51,440
It's not your fault.

71
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:54,190
Those two have fought their whole lives.

72
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:56,140
When two gods fight,

73
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:58,690
who knows when it'll end.

74
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:03,950
All right. Let's go home to find your mother.

75
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:13,740
♫ Our dreamscapes turned out to be so short,
the years pattering by, I lost myself ♫

